      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TORQUED UP (2) returns today after a couple of poor performances to end last preparation in Broome. His form prior to that was super and rates highly for a race of this level. The claim comes in handy from Cheung and he can land closer to the speed. Looks hard to hold out. DYNAMITE BAY (1) was far too good at Kojonup last time out when getting the job done by 2.4L in fine style. The inside draw should see him close to the speed and he's unbeaten at this track and trip. Can repeat the dose without surprise. LADY TORNADO (4) finished sixth over 1400m at Newman at her most recent appearance on August 23. Worth plenty of thought. DOUBLE RUSH (3) lines up for the first time since August 23. Started the last campaign in good style when in the placings over 1400m at Derby. Sure to make his presence felt in the small field.",
